Seventy Seven Energy Inc. Key Developments

Seventy Seven Energy To Be Deleted From Other OTC
Apr 21 17
Seventy Seven Energy Inc. new common stock will be deleted from Other OTC, effective April 24, 2017. The deletion was due to Acquisition/Merger/Amalgamation.


Seventy Seven Energy Inc. Amends and Restates Certificate of Incorporation
Apr 20 17
Seventy Seven Energy Inc. announced the certificate of incorporation of SSE was amended and restated in the form of the Certificate of Incorporation. The bylaws of SSE were amended and restated in the form of the Bylaws.


Seventy Seven Energy Inc. Announces Management Changes
Apr 20 17
On April 20, 2017, pursuant to an agreement and plan of merger, dated as of December 12, 2016, by and among Seventy Seven Energy Inc., Patterson-UTI Energy Inc., and Pyramid Merger Sub Inc., Patterson-UTI completed its Merger with SSE, which was accomplished through the merger of Merger Sub with and into SSE, with SSE surviving the Merger as a wholly-owned subsidiary of Patterson-UTI. In connection with the Merger, all of the directors of SSE immediately prior to the Effective Time ceased to be directors of SSE at the Effective Time and were replaced by William Andrew Hendricks, Jr., John E. Vollmer III and Seth D. Wexler. In connection with the Merger, Jerry Winchester, President and Chief Executive Officer, Cary Baetz, Chief Financial Officer and Treasurer, and Karl Blanchard, Chief Operating Officer, ceased to be officers of SSE at the Effective Time. As of the Effective Time, Mr. Hendricks became President and Chief Executive Officer, Mr. Vollmer became Senior Vice President – Corporate Development, Chief Financial Officer and Treasurer and Mr. Wexler became Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary of SSE.


