THIS IS













Nomac Drilling





Performance Technologies





Great Plains Oilfield Rental












We’ve Got You Covered
Seventy Seven Energy is an Oklahoma-based company that offers drilling, pressure-pumping and oilfield rental tools. Through our umbrella of affiliates, we have the resources to provide comprehensive upstream services for all major shale plays in the United States.







Our Services Include:







Drilling


Through Nomac Drilling, we provide integrated drilling services in conventional and horizontal applications. The plans we provide maximize drilling efficiencies and lower your costs. Our fleet of rigs has an average age of less than seven years and is equipped to meet your needs. To put it simply – we drill faster, safer and more efficiently than our competition.

Nomac Drilling










Pumping


Performance Technologies provides pressure-pumping services for natural gas and oil well stimulation treatments to improve well productivity. We design treatments specific to new and developing unconventional fields. With nine crews across several major shale plays, we’ve got you covered for pressure-pumping services.

Performance Technologies










Rentals


Great Plains Oilfield Rentals provides custom plans for every drilling project, including both equipment and workers. From drill pipe to air packages, Great Plains offers everything you need for a successful drilling operation. Our services include air drilling, water transfer and rentals of drill pipe, drill collars, tubing, blowout preventers, frac tanks, flow back and custom mud systems.

Great Plains Oilfield Rental










LEARNING


Developing. Growing. Improving. Advancing. Achieving. Succeeding. That’s the opportunity afforded every employee within SSE and all its subsidiary companies. We value our workforce and passionately believe our people provide us with our strongest advantage. We are ready to invest in you – in building your knowledge and developing your career so you can continue to add value to our business every day.  What does this investment look like? Our globally-recognized, IADC-accredited well control program, highly-acclaimed leadership initiatives, career development programs, and required training programs in safety to name only a few.

PEOPLE AND LEARNING





















































